# Day 18 - Check if the Middle Element Appears Exactly Once

## Problem Statement
You are given an integer array `nums` of odd length `n`.

Return `true` if the middle element of `nums` appears exactly once in the array. Otherwise, return `false`.

## Code

class Solution {
public:
    bool isMiddleElementUnique(vector<int>& nums) {
        int middle = nums[nums.size() / 2];
        unordered_map<int, int> freq;

        for (int i : nums) {
            freq[i]++;
        }

        if (freq[middle] == 1) {
            return true;
        } else {
            return false;
        }
    }
};



## Time Complexity
**O(n)**

## Space Complexity
**O(n)**

## Approach
This solution first identifies the middle element of the array using its index `nums.size() / 2`. It then uses an **unordered_map** to count the frequency of every element in the array. After computing all frequencies, the frequency of the middle element is checked. If it appears exactly once, the function returns `true`; otherwise, it returns `false`.
